1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,378
- [Felix] <i>I know who did this.</i>
- Who?!

2
00:00:03,461 --> 00:00:04,379
[Felix] <i>Datu Rahman's son.</i>

3
00:00:04,462 --> 00:00:07,132
[Lara] Find Datu Rahman!
I don't care how you do it.

4
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:09,551
- [in English] Bring him back to me!
- I'll take care of it.

5
00:00:09,634 --> 00:00:11,094
[Norhana] <i>Jalil, be careful, okay?</i>

6
00:00:11,177 --> 00:00:13,680
<i>The people chasing you are dangerous.</i>

7
00:00:14,305 --> 00:00:16,558
[Jalil] <i>Don't worry.</i>
<i>Everything will be okay.</i>

8
00:00:16,641 --> 00:00:18,351
<i>The truth will soon come out.</i>

9
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:20,395
Father, let's go back to the island.

10
00:00:20,478 --> 00:00:21,896
Not yet, my dear.

11
00:00:21,980 --> 00:00:24,566
[Datu Rahman] <i>We still</i>
<i>have unfinished business here.</i>

12
00:00:24,649 --> 00:00:27,819
- Where is it?
- The CCTV cameras were deactivated.

13
00:00:27,902 --> 00:00:29,487
Someone from the inside did this.

14
00:00:29,571 --> 00:00:35,285
[Manuel] I will make sure
that our efforts won't go to waste.

15
00:00:35,368 --> 00:00:37,662
[Jalil] <i>Do you know who did this to you?</i>

16
00:00:37,746 --> 00:00:39,247
<i>How many times did they abduct you?</i>

17
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:41,416
Father, what do they need from you?

18
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:44,794
[Datu Rahman] <i>My silence</i>
<i>will protect my children.</i>

19
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:46,087
What happened?

20
00:00:46,171 --> 00:00:49,758
One of the men who abducted
Datu Rahman took him.

21
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:51,509
Was he wearing a mask?

22
00:00:52,093 --> 00:00:53,511
It could be Jalil Abubakar.

23
00:00:53,595 --> 00:01:00,310
[Ahmad] You can't tell anyone
the true identity of Major Allan Espina,

24
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:02,062
not even your friend, Marcus.

25
00:01:02,145 --> 00:01:08,318
You need to help Allan Espina.
You need to help Jalil in his mission.

26
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:10,153
Can I count on you, brother?

27
00:01:13,531 --> 00:01:16,659
[mysterious theme music playing]

28
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:33,176
I'm sorry, buddy.

29
00:01:33,718 --> 00:01:35,261
I couldn't rescue Datu Rahman.

30
00:01:37,013 --> 00:01:38,723
There's nothing we can do about it, buddy.

31
00:01:39,766 --> 00:01:41,935
They found the safe house.

32
00:01:43,019 --> 00:01:44,229
[Marcus sighs]

33
00:01:44,312 --> 00:01:48,817
I suppose it's better
that it's Datu Rahman's son who took him.

34
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:51,694
That means Datu Rahman's alive.

35
00:01:52,278 --> 00:01:54,322
And the time will come
when we get the information

36
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:55,824
that he is hiding.

37
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:07,627
[knocking on door]

38
00:02:11,297 --> 00:02:13,424
The food is ready, Father.

39
00:02:13,508 --> 00:02:15,635
We should eat while it's still hot.

40
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:17,470
Alright.

41
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:21,182
[Jamila] Come on.

42
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:25,854
[gentle music playing]

43
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:43,955
I still can't believe
that you're with us, Father.

44
00:02:44,497 --> 00:02:46,708
Jalil kept his promise.

45
00:02:47,667 --> 00:02:48,877
[Jamilah chuckles]

46
00:02:49,836 --> 00:02:52,297
This will all soon pass, Jamilah.

47
00:02:55,925 --> 00:02:58,094
[In Tausug] Thank you, Omar and Norhana.

48
00:02:58,845 --> 00:03:04,809
I will forever be in debt to you
for taking care of my children.

49
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:08,354
That's nothing, Rahman. We're family!

50
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:10,315
Jamilah is my niece,
and Jalil is my nephew.

51
00:03:11,316 --> 00:03:14,652
Exactly, Datu. No matter what happens…

52
00:03:15,612 --> 00:03:17,238
we are family.

53
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:19,782
- Let's eat.
- [In Tausug] Thank you.

54
00:03:20,575 --> 00:03:22,076
- [Norhana] Let's eat.
- Uncle, let's eat!

55
00:03:22,160 --> 00:03:23,328
[phone ringing]

56
00:03:28,499 --> 00:03:29,626
Hello?

57
00:03:30,376 --> 00:03:31,502
Hm!

58
00:03:33,421 --> 00:03:36,174
- It's Jalil. He wants to talk to you.
- [Datu Rahman] Hm?

59
00:03:37,425 --> 00:03:40,428
[music turns unsettling]

60
00:03:55,526 --> 00:03:56,945
I sent you something.

61
00:03:57,445 --> 00:03:58,947
Take a good look at it.

62
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:02,617
I know he's Datu Rahman's son.

63
00:04:06,579 --> 00:04:07,747
I know this guy.

64
00:04:08,873 --> 00:04:10,458
I've encountered him before.

65
00:04:13,711 --> 00:04:16,089
- [Jalil] Surrender!
- What do you take us for?!

66
00:04:16,172 --> 00:04:17,799
You think you can stop us?!

67
00:04:18,841 --> 00:04:21,010
We are so much bigger than you think!

68
00:04:21,094 --> 00:04:22,178
You don't know anything!

69
00:04:22,262 --> 00:04:24,430
The real fight hasn't started yet!

70
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:28,935
He's Jalil Abubakar.

71
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:30,770
<i>A member of CDSU.</i>

72
00:04:33,523 --> 00:04:34,691
[Arthur] <i>From what I know,</i>

73
00:04:35,316 --> 00:04:37,318
<i>he's still teaching recruits</i>

74
00:04:37,402 --> 00:04:39,654
<i>in various parts of Mindanao.</i>

75
00:04:39,737 --> 00:04:42,615
[unsettling music continues]

76
00:04:59,465 --> 00:05:01,009
I've confirmed it, sir.

77
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:04,846
This is the bullet shell I've retrieved.

78
00:05:06,931 --> 00:05:09,934
A different group caused the riot
on the island that night.

79
00:05:11,602 --> 00:05:13,271
These are also the photos

80
00:05:13,354 --> 00:05:16,607
of the smuggled firearms
buried in a mountain.

81
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:22,822
Sir, Datu Rahman is telling the truth.

82
00:05:23,448 --> 00:05:26,034
They're not the ones
smuggling those firearms.

83
00:05:28,745 --> 00:05:31,873
They just hide it,
so syndicates can't use it.

84
00:05:32,957 --> 00:05:36,252
Sir… Datu Rahman is innocent.

85
00:05:36,335 --> 00:05:39,964
[pensive music playing]

86
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:41,799
That means, sir,

87
00:05:41,883 --> 00:05:44,469
someone planted the intel we had.

88
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:47,221
Colonel Del Mundo
was an accomplice to this.

89
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:51,642
He was the one who gave us the wrong intel
about Datu Rahman.

90
00:05:51,726 --> 00:05:52,852
That's why he was killed.

91
00:05:53,728 --> 00:05:54,854
He was silenced.

92
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:58,900
[pensive music playing]

93
00:06:05,448 --> 00:06:06,866
The question is…

94
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:11,120
Who does he work for?

95
00:06:11,621 --> 00:06:14,332
[pensive music continues]

96
00:06:17,585 --> 00:06:19,462
I confirmed another thing
on the island, sir.

97
00:06:21,339 --> 00:06:23,091
[smuggler] <i>You'll confiscate our firearms?</i>

98
00:06:23,674 --> 00:06:25,009
You think you'll succeed

99
00:06:25,510 --> 00:06:27,178
when our allies are also from your agency?

100
00:06:28,930 --> 00:06:31,182
They even have high ranks within the NLEA.

101
00:06:31,265 --> 00:06:35,394
So, no matter how many times
you confiscate these firearms,

102
00:06:36,062 --> 00:06:37,730
these will eventually come back to us.

103
00:06:38,773 --> 00:06:40,608
[Marcus] Those words
came directly from the mouth

104
00:06:40,691 --> 00:06:43,778
of the high-ranking smuggler
I fought on the island.

105
00:06:45,029 --> 00:06:48,616
Their protector is from NLEA.

106
00:06:48,699 --> 00:06:50,118
Someone with a high-ranking position.

107
00:06:50,201 --> 00:06:52,745
That's why these smugglers are brave.

108
00:06:53,329 --> 00:06:57,250
Now, I don't know if…
they have other allies outside of NLEA,

109
00:06:57,333 --> 00:06:59,043
but I'm sure, sir,

110
00:07:00,086 --> 00:07:03,047
there is a wolf in sheep's clothing
on our side of the fence.

111
00:07:07,885 --> 00:07:11,431
[pensive music continues]

112
00:07:26,737 --> 00:07:28,698
There's something else
you should know, sir.

113
00:07:34,745 --> 00:07:36,122
You're not done yet?

114
00:07:36,706 --> 00:07:37,707
Sir…

115
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:44,630
I'm the one who took Datu Rahman
from the Zylverix building.

116
00:07:45,548 --> 00:07:49,093
I only saved him from the people
who abducted him.

117
00:07:52,388 --> 00:07:54,265
Agent Reyes!

118
00:07:56,517 --> 00:07:57,560
[grunts]

119
00:08:03,816 --> 00:08:05,443
Where is Datu Rahman now?

120
00:08:06,027 --> 00:08:07,069
Where is he?!

121
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:18,080
While I was on the island,
he was tracked down by his kidnappers.

122
00:08:19,832 --> 00:08:22,043
[in English] Goddammit, Reyes!

123
00:08:23,377 --> 00:08:24,879
But he was saved…

124
00:08:25,963 --> 00:08:27,548
by his son.

125
00:08:32,595 --> 00:08:33,971
It's Jalil Abubakar.

126
00:08:36,641 --> 00:08:37,683
How--

127
00:08:38,976 --> 00:08:40,311
He's also a fugitive.

128
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:43,105
Both of them need to be arrested!

129
00:08:43,189 --> 00:08:45,316
That's why we need to know
where they are, sir.

130
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:48,486
They're certainly both in danger.

131
00:08:52,365 --> 00:08:53,616
[Azuelo sighs]

132
00:08:54,116 --> 00:08:55,159
Agent Reyes.

133
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:57,745
I'm not sure anymore

134
00:08:57,828 --> 00:09:02,250
if I should be mad at you or applaud you!

135
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:06,045
You've lied to me, Agent Reyes!

136
00:09:06,128 --> 00:09:10,800
You've concealed and hidden
very important information from me!

137
00:09:12,552 --> 00:09:15,888
Now, give me one good reason

138
00:09:16,847 --> 00:09:20,726
- why I shouldn't suspend you right now!
- [loud thud]

139
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:31,279
I'm the only one you can count on, sir.

140
00:09:32,738 --> 00:09:36,492
I'm the only one who can
help you solve this case.

141
00:09:39,036 --> 00:09:41,247
What we really need to know, sir…

142
00:09:43,165 --> 00:09:46,877
Who is the mastermind behind all of this?

143
00:09:46,961 --> 00:09:47,795
‪[dramatic sting]

144
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:02,143
[music turns suspenseful]

145
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:15,531
[tense music playing]

146
00:10:47,188 --> 00:10:48,439
[Marcus] <i>Edrick.</i>

147
00:10:49,273 --> 00:10:51,817
- Anything?
- [Edrick] <i>Sir. Did you see that?</i>

148
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:57,031
There is no trace
of the crazy person you told me.

149
00:10:58,658 --> 00:10:59,909
Check it thoroughly.

150
00:11:05,247 --> 00:11:07,166
[Edrick] <i>Sir, I was just wondering…</i>

151
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:09,085
<i>how that happened.</i>

152
00:11:09,168 --> 00:11:10,419
[breathes deeply]

153
00:11:10,503 --> 00:11:12,380
How are they so strong?

154
00:11:13,089 --> 00:11:15,216
How did they clean up
the traces of killings?

155
00:11:18,844 --> 00:11:20,221
[sighs]

156
00:11:22,598 --> 00:11:25,267
[scream echoes] Why?!

157
00:11:29,146 --> 00:11:31,649
Hey! You're being loud again.

158
00:11:31,732 --> 00:11:33,692
Calm down. Be quiet.

159
00:11:34,235 --> 00:11:36,862
If someone hears you,
you'll be asking why in heaven.

160
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:39,156
I'm sorry, sir. I was just joking.

161
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:42,535
Sir. They do seem pretty tough.

162
00:11:42,618 --> 00:11:43,786
Be careful, sir.

163
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:48,624
[tense music continues]

164
00:11:55,756 --> 00:11:57,425
[music turns somber]

165
00:11:57,508 --> 00:12:01,262
[Azuelo] <i>These problems</i>
<i>really came up now.</i>

166
00:12:02,638 --> 00:12:07,309
<i>Right before I'm about to be</i>
<i>a General and retire soon.</i>

167
00:12:09,353 --> 00:12:10,938
<i>But I can't just walk away from all this.</i>

168
00:12:12,982 --> 00:12:17,278
<i>I can't leave NLEA and SID rotting.</i>

169
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:21,282
<i>If I leave now,</i>

170
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,994
<i>many more people will get hurt.</i>

171
00:12:27,746 --> 00:12:29,790
<i>That bastard Reyes.</i>

172
00:12:30,791 --> 00:12:32,543
<i>I was supposed to be at peace.</i>

173
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:35,921
<i>Why do you have to tell me all of that?</i>

174
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:45,431
Why do I have to know all this?!

175
00:12:48,517 --> 00:12:50,728
- [grunts angrily]
- [objects falling]

176
00:12:54,064 --> 00:12:55,483
[phone vibrating]

177
00:13:06,076 --> 00:13:07,495
Sweetheart, what is it?

178
00:13:07,578 --> 00:13:08,871
<i>I'm sorry, sweetheart.</i>

179
00:13:09,955 --> 00:13:11,373
Our son…

180
00:13:12,082 --> 00:13:13,876
got into a fight at school.

181
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:15,628
What?

182
00:13:15,711 --> 00:13:17,171
Come on.

183
00:13:17,254 --> 00:13:18,297
[Azuelo] <i>Kyle.</i>

184
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:20,466
<i>Why did you get into a fight?</i>

185
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:23,844
<i>I've already got a lot of problems,</i>
<i>son, and now this?</i>

186
00:13:24,845 --> 00:13:26,805
My classmates pissed me off.

187
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:29,266
[breathing sharply] They kept annoying me.

188
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:31,435
That's not enough reason
to get into a fight.

189
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,312
Just ignore them.

190
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:35,397
[Kyle] <i>How can I ignore them?</i>

191
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:37,775
- They were calling you names!
- [tense music playing]

192
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:41,445
<i>They said you're a no-good cop.</i>

193
00:13:42,404 --> 00:13:44,490
<i>How can I just ignore that?</i> [sobs]

194
00:13:45,074 --> 00:13:47,493
<i>They said Datu Rahman got away</i>

195
00:13:48,661 --> 00:13:49,787
<i>because you're inept…</i>

196
00:13:50,746 --> 00:13:52,164
<i>and incompetent…</i>

197
00:13:52,248 --> 00:13:53,958
[sobbing, sniffling]

198
00:13:54,041 --> 00:13:55,793
<i>…and that you're not smart.</i>

199
00:13:55,876 --> 00:13:57,878
- [music turns somber]
- [sobbing]

200
00:13:57,962 --> 00:13:59,421
I can't just ignore that, Pa.

201
00:13:59,505 --> 00:14:00,339
‪[Kyle sobbing]

202
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:04,593
[Kyle] <i>I can't just let them say</i>
<i>those hurtful words against you.</i>

203
00:14:06,428 --> 00:14:08,472
<i>But that's not true, Pa, right?</i>

204
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,016
You're great.

205
00:14:12,726 --> 00:14:14,353
<i>You're smart.</i>

206
00:14:15,854 --> 00:14:17,898
And above all, Pa,

207
00:14:18,732 --> 00:14:20,401
you have integrity.

208
00:14:21,902 --> 00:14:23,487
[Kyle] <i>That's why I look up to you.</i>

209
00:14:24,154 --> 00:14:27,199
<i>So I'd punch everyone</i>
<i>who spreads lies about you.</i>

210
00:14:32,746 --> 00:14:34,123
[exhales deeply]

211
00:14:35,165 --> 00:14:36,208
Okay, son.

212
00:14:36,709 --> 00:14:38,711
We'll talk again when I come home, okay?

213
00:14:42,298 --> 00:14:45,009
[Kyle sobbing]

214
00:14:53,934 --> 00:14:56,896
[pensive music playing]

215
00:14:58,480 --> 00:15:01,233
[Azuelo] <i>My son thinks of me highly.</i>

216
00:15:04,528 --> 00:15:05,779
[exhales]

217
00:15:09,992 --> 00:15:11,744
[line ringing]

218
00:15:12,453 --> 00:15:13,495
Reyes.

219
00:15:15,497 --> 00:15:16,916
Come here right now.

220
00:15:17,875 --> 00:15:19,418
We have something to do.

221
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:26,717
[in English] Goddammit.

222
00:15:26,800 --> 00:15:28,802
[music intensifies, concludes]

223
00:15:29,845 --> 00:15:33,057
Check the CCTV footage. Around 10 p.m.

224
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:34,683
The possible exits in the shipyard.

225
00:15:34,767 --> 00:15:36,101
Copy, ma'am.

226
00:15:39,688 --> 00:15:41,649
Ma'am, what exactly are we looking for?

227
00:15:41,732 --> 00:15:43,901
[scoffs] Obviously, I don't know either.

228
00:15:43,984 --> 00:15:45,527
That's why I asked you to check it.

229
00:15:45,611 --> 00:15:49,448
Check all the possible exits
because I want to know the movement there.

230
00:15:50,115 --> 00:15:52,952
Ma'am, where do we start looking?

231
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,828
A lot of cars are passing by.

232
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:57,247
We don't have any reference

233
00:15:57,998 --> 00:16:00,334
because you had the CCTVs disabled
in the shipyard.

234
00:16:00,834 --> 00:16:03,796
[tense mysterious music playing]

235
00:16:06,882 --> 00:16:07,967
Okay, okay.

236
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:10,344
No more questions. I'll just shut up.

237
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:25,526
- T-This car. Follow it.
- [Buster] Copy, ma'am.

238
00:16:48,382 --> 00:16:50,426
[Lara huffing]

239
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:54,388
Hey, Buster.

240
00:16:54,471 --> 00:16:56,223
No one must know about this, alright?

241
00:16:56,306 --> 00:16:57,975
[in English] This is top secret.

242
00:16:58,058 --> 00:16:59,977
My mission would be compromised
if someone found out.

243
00:17:00,060 --> 00:17:02,062
- [in English] Do you understand?
- [in English] Understood, ma'am.

244
00:17:15,534 --> 00:17:18,537
- [gloomy music playing]
- [digital chiming]

245
00:17:25,335 --> 00:17:26,462
Where's Buster?

246
00:17:27,254 --> 00:17:29,923
Uh, he just went on a lunch break, sir.

247
00:17:32,801 --> 00:17:34,845
- Is that so?
- Yeah.

248
00:17:35,804 --> 00:17:37,473
You're new here, aren't you?

249
00:17:37,556 --> 00:17:38,515
[chuckles softly] Yes, sir.

250
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:40,726
I'm your new IT specialist here, sir.

251
00:17:40,809 --> 00:17:42,728
I'm Ethan, sir. Nice to meet you.

252
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:44,646
Okay.

253
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,982
Now, since you're new here,

254
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:49,026
I'd like you to make a good impression.

255
00:17:50,277 --> 00:17:51,361
Do you see this?

256
00:17:52,488 --> 00:17:54,948
Find this guy in the CDSU database.

257
00:17:56,033 --> 00:17:57,701
Jalil Abubakar.

258
00:17:58,869 --> 00:17:59,787
Get to work.

259
00:18:00,454 --> 00:18:02,372
[suspenseful music playing]

260
00:18:02,956 --> 00:18:06,168
When Mister Omar asks, I can't say no.

261
00:18:06,251 --> 00:18:07,419
Besides… [scoffs]

262
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:09,838
Look, it's easy peasy.

263
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:12,758
[Ethan exhales deeply]

264
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:14,384
What's wrong?

265
00:18:15,469 --> 00:18:17,137
- Uh, nothing, sir. It's--
- Do you know him?

266
00:18:17,221 --> 00:18:20,891
No. I just really wish I had
a beard like his.

267
00:18:20,974 --> 00:18:22,559
Let me find him now, sir.

268
00:18:22,643 --> 00:18:25,854
[suspenseful music continues]

269
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:28,524
[Ethan] "Jalil Abubakar."

270
00:18:34,446 --> 00:18:37,324
"Jalil Abubakar."

271
00:18:40,119 --> 00:18:41,328
One more time.

272
00:18:41,411 --> 00:18:44,164
"Jalil Abubakar."

273
00:18:45,666 --> 00:18:50,796
Sir, the CDSU database shows
no record of Jalil Abubakar.

274
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:52,589
Try it again!

275
00:18:53,298 --> 00:18:55,676
- Alright, sir.
- Hurry up.

276
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,386
"Jalil Abubakar."

277
00:19:01,014 --> 00:19:04,268
[suspenseful music continues]

278
00:19:08,313 --> 00:19:09,731
No luck, sir.

279
00:19:09,815 --> 00:19:10,649
‪[dramatic sting]

280
00:19:15,028 --> 00:19:16,071
[knocking on door]

281
00:19:18,782 --> 00:19:21,702
[unsettling music playing]

282
00:19:25,664 --> 00:19:29,084
Madam. I've identified
the son of Datu Rahman.

283
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:32,880
His name is Jalil Abubakar.

284
00:19:34,464 --> 00:19:37,509
I had the CDSU's new hire
run a background check.

285
00:19:40,679 --> 00:19:41,847
It's strange.

286
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:44,474
When I checked his files,

287
00:19:45,934 --> 00:19:47,394
I couldn't find anything.

288
00:19:48,061 --> 00:19:49,605
No results came up.

289
00:19:51,815 --> 00:19:52,691
It's like he doesn't exist at all.

290
00:19:52,774 --> 00:19:53,609
‪[dramatic sting]

291
00:20:02,993 --> 00:20:04,369
[music intensifying]

292
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:05,871
How's that possible?

293
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:09,750
It was deliberately erased.

294
00:20:12,044 --> 00:20:15,172
Someone must be helping him
so that he can move around freely.

295
00:20:24,848 --> 00:20:26,183
We need to find him.

296
00:20:27,684 --> 00:20:28,852
[in English] Definitely, madam.

297
00:20:40,906 --> 00:20:42,366
What are you implying?

298
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:45,077
That there is a traitor in this agency?

299
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,954
[tense music playing]

300
00:20:47,913 --> 00:20:51,124
At first, I did not want to believe it.

301
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:53,543
But there is evidence.

302
00:20:56,129 --> 00:20:59,383
All I want is for them to be caught

303
00:20:59,466 --> 00:21:04,805
before the NLEA and the SID
are completely destroyed.

304
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:12,312
[in English] These are
serious accusations.

305
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:18,860
We have confirmed
Datu Rahman's statement is accurate.

306
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:25,158
Colonel Del Mundo's intelligence report

307
00:21:25,242 --> 00:21:27,327
was intended to set him up!

308
00:21:29,788 --> 00:21:32,249
Then, conveniently,

309
00:21:32,332 --> 00:21:35,627
he committed suicide
before he could be questioned.

310
00:21:41,216 --> 00:21:45,137
[in English] Colonel Del Mundo
was a very good police officer!

311
00:21:45,220 --> 00:21:47,431
Don't trample on his name!

312
00:21:47,514 --> 00:21:50,267
He must have had the support
of someone powerful!

313
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:51,184
[sniffles]

314
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:52,894
That's why he did what he did!

315
00:21:52,978 --> 00:21:57,232
And most likely, he still
has accomplices in this very room!

316
00:21:57,316 --> 00:21:59,234
‪[dramatic stinging]

317
00:21:59,901 --> 00:22:00,736
[in English] How dare you!

318
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:07,617
You'll create enemies
with your accusations.

319
00:22:07,701 --> 00:22:09,077
Both of you!

320
00:22:09,161 --> 00:22:11,413
[suspenseful music playing]

321
00:22:13,498 --> 00:22:16,043
To hell with that!

322
00:22:17,294 --> 00:22:18,879
I am about to retire.

323
00:22:19,671 --> 00:22:24,968
I will make sure the SID
and the NLEA are left in good order

324
00:22:25,052 --> 00:22:26,762
when I leave!

325
00:22:26,845 --> 00:22:28,764
[dramatic music playing]

326
00:22:28,847 --> 00:22:34,770
‪[dramatic stinging]

327
00:22:59,252 --> 00:23:00,629
[Usman] <i>I can't lie to Marcus.</i>

328
00:23:00,712 --> 00:23:02,297
Why don't we just tell him the truth?

329
00:23:02,380 --> 00:23:03,465
After all, you both want the same thing.

330
00:23:03,548 --> 00:23:07,344
He might not be in cahoots
with the bastards who murdered our people.

331
00:23:07,427 --> 00:23:08,929
[Jalil] <i>Still, he was manipulated by them.</i>

332
00:23:09,012 --> 00:23:10,555
I can't trust him.

333
00:23:10,639 --> 00:23:12,974
[Datu Rahman] <i>My name is Rahman Abubakar.</i>

334
00:23:13,058 --> 00:23:16,603
<i>There's no truth to the accusations</i>
<i>they're making against me.</i>

335
00:23:16,686 --> 00:23:22,067
<i>Their weapons are being dropped</i>
<i>into the sea near our island.</i>

336
00:23:22,651 --> 00:23:26,530
<i>Agent Marcus Reyes,</i>
<i>the people responsible for this</i>

337
00:23:26,613 --> 00:23:28,573
<i>might be in the NLEA.</i>

338
00:23:29,825 --> 00:23:34,204
Do you really want to ruin
the reputation of the NLEA and the SID?!

339
00:23:34,287 --> 00:23:36,498
[in English] I feel like
I'm losing control of everything!

340
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:37,624
Reyes is under my command!

341
00:23:37,707 --> 00:23:40,377
[Azuelo, in English]
<i>You are overstepping boundaries!</i>

342
00:23:41,586 --> 00:23:44,172
[Manuel] <i>The worse</i>
<i>the crimes being committed,</i>

343
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:48,385
<i>the more people will lose</i>
<i>confidence in the government.</i>

344
00:23:48,468 --> 00:23:53,014
<i>Power will soon be in our hands.</i>
